      "body" : "No, being in an sbin directory does not mean it is intended to executed by root. At least not traditionally on UNIX systems, maybe some of the newer ones are incorrectly making that distinction.\r\n\r\nDaemons usually fork to run in their own user/group - as apache (httpd), named, and bitcoind do - from a service script that is started by root. And they traditionally go into an `sbin` directory so that a user who might want to execute the command `bitcoin-cli` or `bitcoin-tx` doesn't have `bitcoind` in their path.",
